                <h2 class="txt-black">The Maverick Awards Categories</h2>
                <p class="sub-intro-head txt-gold"><b>1. The Maverick Start Up of The Year Award</b></p>
                <p>This award category is designed to recognise and honour the ‘rising star’ young
					entrepreneurs across all sectors whose enterprises have been in operation for a 
					minimum period of 1 year and not longer than 3 years, turning over a minimum 
					of R1million per annum, with no maximum threshold on their turnover. 
					Entrepreneurs entering this category are NOT ELIGIBLE to enter the other 
					award categories below due to the 3 year minimum operational period required 
					for all other categories.</p><br />
                <p class="sub-intro-head txt-gold"><b>2. The Maverick Award for Employment Creation Excellence</b></p>
                <p>This category is open to qualifying young entrepreneurs that have been in business for 3 years or more, turning in excess of R3million revenue per year, employing a minimum of 20 employees. And while they have created a significant number of jobs they must also display a significant investment and dedication towards the uplifting, up-skilling and training of their employees.</p><br />
                <p class="sub-intro-head txt-gold"><b>3. The Maverick Without Borders Award for Export Excellence</b></p>
                <p>This category is open to qualifying young entrepreneurs that have been in business for 3 years or more, turning a minimum of R3million revenue per year, primarily operating in South Africa, however they have must have successfully established distribution of their products/services in foreign markets such that a significant proportion of their revenue comes from foreign markets.</p><br />	
                <p class="sub-intro-head txt-gold"><b>4. The Maverick Award for Social Enterprise Excellence</b></p>
                <p>This category is open to qualifying young social entrepreneurs that have been in business for 1 years or more turning a minimum of R1million revenue/grants/donations per year, they must clearly demonstrate a remarkable ability in the development & deployment of solutions, products and services that address social issues in South Africa.</p><br />
                <p class="sub-intro-head txt-gold"><b>5. The Maverick Award for Service Excellence</b></p>
                <p>This category is open to qualifying young service based entrepreneurs that have been in business for 3 years or more, turning a minimum of R3million revenue, while clearly having developed and deployed novel, ground-breaking and innovative methodologies of delivering a service in any sector of the economy to their customers in a manner that clearly displays a marked improvement in user experience or value derived thereof.</p><br />
                <p class="sub-intro-head txt-gold"><b>6. The Maverick Award for Manufacturing and Industrial Excellence</b></p>
                <p>This category is open to qualifying young entrepreneurs that have been in business for 3 years or more, turning a minimum of R3million revenue within the manufacturing and industrial sectors of the economy.</p><br />	
               <p class="sub-intro-head txt-gold"><b>7. The Maverick Award for Built Environment Excellence</b></p>
                <p>This category is open to qualifying young entrepreneurs that have been in business for 3 years or more, turning a minimum of R3million revenue in the built-environment sectors of the economy – Construction, Architecture, Quantity Surveying, Civil, Mechanical, Electrical Engineering and Draughtsmen just to mention a few.</p><br />
               <p class="sub-intro-head txt-gold"><b>8. The Maverick Award for Agricultural Excellence</b></p>
                <p>This category is open to qualifying young entrepreneurs that have been in business for 3 years or more, turning a minimum of R3million revenue in the agricultural sectors of the economy – Crop and Livestock Farming, Agro-Processing, Agro-Value Chain Products/Services  and  Processed Agro-Distribution and other related sectors.</p><br />					
               <p class="sub-intro-head txt-gold"><b>9. The Maverick Award for Green Enterprise Excellence</b></p>
                <p>This category is open to qualifying young entrepreneurs that have been in business for 3 years or more, turning a minimum of R3million revenue in the green sectors of the economy such as renewable & alternative energy, environmental conservation, energy conservation and other related sectors.</p><br />
               <p class="sub-intro-head txt-gold"><b>10. The Maverick Award for Technology Excellence</b></p>
                <p>This category is open to qualifying young entrepreneurs that have been in business for 3 years or more, turning a minimum of R3million revenue in the technology spaces across all sectors of the economy.</p><br />		
               <p class="sub-intro-head txt-gold"><b>11. The Maverick Award for Blue Ocean Innovation Excellence</b></p>
                <p>This category is open to qualifying young entrepreneurs that have been in business for 3 years or more, turning a minimum of R3million revenue, while having developed and deployed novel and ground-breaking innovations of such great proportions that have never been witnessed before within a known industry or market space, such that a completely new, previously unknown and uncontested market space is created through this new disruptive business model, method(s) or invention(s).</p><br />					
